{%- comment -%}
  Product ingredients resolver.

  Maps product.handle -> full ingredient list extracted from product PDFs.
  Outputs a pipe-separated string where each ingredient is "Name - Dose".
  The caller splits on '|' and renders each item.

  Matching strategy: flexible `contains` checks on short keywords so any
  handle variation (renames, pack-size differences) still resolves.

  Usage:
    {%- capture ingredients_str -%}{%- render 'product-ingredients-data', product: product -%}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- assign ingredients = ingredients_str | split: '|' -%}
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign handle = product.handle | downcase
  assign ingredients = ''

  comment
    Priority 1: product metafield (admin-managed) can override.
  endcomment
  assign meta_ing = product.metafields.custom.ingredients | default: ''
  if meta_ing != ''
    assign ingredients = meta_ing
  endif

  comment
    Priority 2: match by short keyword contained in handle.
    Ordered so more specific keys win first (e.g. 'icee-rd' before 'icee').
  endcomment
  if ingredients == ''
    if handle contains 'steno-villa' and handle contains 'tablet'
      assign ingredients = 'Hajratber stone|Gokhru (Tribulus terrestris)|Pashanbhed root|Chandraprabha powder|Palash pushpa|Moolishar panchang|Shilajit|Varun chhal|Kulthi|Punarnava|Apamarga|Kankol|Yavakshar|Saindhav|Sajikhar|Nausadar'
